{"TopicId":208561,"ForumId":112,"TopicTitle":"Suggestion - Square orbits (Sun - Planet - Moon system)","CreatedByName":"Pi0neer","CreatedById":211726,"CreatedDateTime":"2022-06-12T12:32:22Z","PageNum":1,"Articles":[{"CreatedByName":"Pi0neer","CreatedById":211726,"CreatedDateTime":"2022-06-12T12:32:22Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nIn a sun - planet - moon system, the orbit of the moon can look like a square relative to the star, as was demonstrated in \u003Ca href=\u0022https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=t99CmgJAXbg\u0022 rel=\u0022external nofollow\u0022\u003Ethis video\u003C/a\u003E.\u003Cbr\u003E\u003Cbr\u003E\nIt would be quite a sight if, from the moon, you could time-warp and see yourself going further, and closer to the star in a square shape.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Bej Kerman","CreatedById":182413,"CreatedDateTime":"2022-06-12T16:03:12Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00224143915\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022208561\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221655037142\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u0022211726\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022Pi0neer\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n3 hours ago, Pi0neer said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003Ca href=\u0022https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=t99CmgJAXbg\u0022 rel=\u0022external nofollow\u0022\u003Ethis video\u003C/a\u003E.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nDoes the guy ever get around to how massive the planet would need to be for the moon to have such a big orbit and the influence such a massive planet would have on its parent star? Massive doubts on my end.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"HebaruSan","CreatedById":156657,"CreatedDateTime":"2022-06-12T16:21:43Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00224143995\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022208561\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221655049792\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u0022182413\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022Bej Kerman\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n13 minutes ago, Bej Kerman said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nDoes the guy ever get around to how massive the planet would need to be for the moon to have such a big orbit and the influence such a massive planet would have on its parent star? Massive doubts on my end.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nYes, around the 16 minute mark:\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsSpoiler\u0022 data-ipsspoiler=\u0022\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsSpoiler_header\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cspan\u003ESpoiler\u003C/span\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsSpoiler_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003Cimg alt=\u0022jdEdr6g.png\u0022 class=\u0022ipsImage\u0022 data-ratio=\u002257.33\u0022 height=\u0022606\u0022 width=\u00221057\u0022 src=\u0022https://i.imgur.com/jdEdr6g.png\u0022\u003E\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nHe covers the Hill sphere right after that.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Laxez","CreatedById":216956,"CreatedDateTime":"2022-06-15T06:59:53Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nthe \u0022problem\u0022 is that the square orbit shown in the video is the orbit of the object in relation to the sun, in KSP the orbit of your object that is shown is relative to the nearest body, so you would see the orbit around in Kerbin, but not in Kerbol\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Vl3d","CreatedById":219348,"CreatedDateTime":"2022-06-15T13:24:43Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nSquare orbits are useful in a patched conics system?\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Ember12","CreatedById":217583,"CreatedDateTime":"2022-06-22T15:52:32Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00224143915\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022208561\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221655037142\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u0022211726\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022Pi0neer\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\nOn 6/12/2022 at 5:32 AM, Pi0neer said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nIt would be quite a sight if, from the moon, you could time-warp and see yourself going further, and closer to the star in a square shape.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nEven if all the problems mentioned above (and more will no doubt be posted below) were overcome, I can\u0027t imagine this as anything more than an oh-yeah-that\u0027s-kinda-cool thing.\u00A0 Probably, no one would even look at it more than once or twice.\u00A0 Not at all worth the difficulty of implementation IMO.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Vl3d","CreatedById":219348,"CreatedDateTime":"2022-06-22T17:52:08Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00224147660\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022208561\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221655913152\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u0022217583\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022Ember12\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citat